              <td><strong>Deendayal Port</strong><br><small>(formerly Kandla)</small></td>
              <td>Gujarat</td>
              <td>1955</td>
              <td>Declared major port 8 April 1955 by Lal Bahadur Shastri (then Transport Minister). Renamed after Pandit Deendayal Upadhyay on 25 September 2017. Tidal port on Gulf of Kutch. <strong>Largest major port by cargo</strong> (crossed 150 MMT in FY 2024-25).</td>
